---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Card from '../components/Card.astro'
import Link from '../components/Link.astro'
import { 
    Target, 
    Users, 
    Github, 
    Building, 
    Scale,
    Settings 
} from 'lucide-astro'
---
<Layout title="About">
    <main class="flex flex-col w-full px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-10 py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
                About Railopedia
            </h1>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8 md:text-lg lg:text-xl">
              Learn more about our mission, team, and how we're revolutionizing the rail travel industry.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Target class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    Our Mission
                </Fragment>
                Our mission is to try and make rail travel more accessible and affordable for everyone.
                We believe that consumers should always have access to the best deals and information when it comes to booking train tickets.
            </Card>
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Users class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    People
                </Fragment>
                Railopedia is currently solely maintained by 
                    <Link href="https://tobyrushton.com">
                        Toby Rushton
                    </Link>, 
                a computer science student at the University of Leeds.
                However, I'm always looking for contributors to help out with the project.
            </Card>
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Github class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    Open Source
                </Fragment>
                Railopedia is entirely open source project, available 
                    <Link href="https://github.com/tobyrushton/railopedia">
                        on GitHub
                    </Link>.
                If you'd like to contribute, feel free to submit open an issue with your idea or submit a pull request.
            </Card>
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Building class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    Providers
                </Fragment>
                We currently search and display results from: 
                <Link href="https://www.thetrainline.com">Trainline</Link>,
                <Link href="https://www.mytrainpal.com">Trainpal</Link>,
                <Link href="https://www.traintickets.com">Traintickets</Link>,
                <Link href="https://www.raileasy.co.uk">Raileasy</Link>.
                However, we're always looking to add more providers to our search.
            </Card>
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Scale class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    Disclaimer
                </Fragment>
                Railopedia is not affiliated with any of the train providers we search. We simply provide a search engine to help you find the best deals.
                We're not responsible for any issues you may have after you leave our site.
            </Card>
            <Card>
                <Fragment slot="title">
                    <Settings class="w-8 h-8 text-gray-500" />
                    Support
                </Fragment>
                As Railopedia is currently in beta, you may experience some bugs or issues.
                If you do, please feel free to 
                    <Link href="https://github.com/tobyrushton/railopedia/issues">
                        open an issue
                    </Link>
                on our GitHub repository.
            </Card>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>